That's not what I want to do.

00:38:19.890 --> 00:38:20.390
Sorry.

00:38:20.390 --> 00:38:25.320
So I actually do mean what I was
going to write down initially.

00:38:25.320 --> 00:38:41.975
So if V is adjacent to
all the earlier vertices

00:38:41.975 --> 00:38:42.600
in this order--

00:38:54.450 --> 00:39:00.090
so for example, this
vertex, it's OK.

00:39:00.090 --> 00:39:04.230
And I'm also going to
include this vertex here,

00:39:04.230 --> 00:39:12.150
because both of its
earlier vertices are in--

00:39:12.150 --> 00:39:16.350
both the earlier vertices are
adjacent to the third vertex.

00:39:16.350 --> 00:39:18.020
And I think that's it.

00:39:20.882 --> 00:39:25.160
Now, this set x, I
claim two things.

00:39:25.160 --> 00:39:29.490
One, that x has to be a clique.

00:39:29.490 --> 00:39:34.050
So claim that x
has to be a clique.

00:39:37.110 --> 00:39:41.200
Because every vertex in
the x is adjacent to all

00:39:41.200 --> 00:39:43.540
of the [INAUDIBLE]
vertices in particular.

00:39:43.540 --> 00:39:48.480
All the vertices in x
are joined to each other.

00:39:48.480 --> 00:39:54.930
On the other hand, how big is
x, at least in expectation?

00:39:54.930 --> 00:40:05.202
So for every vertex, I want
to understand the probability

00:40:05.202 --> 00:40:10.630
that this v is included in x.

00:40:10.630 --> 00:40:14.790
So v has a bunch
of non-neighbors.

00:40:14.790 --> 00:40:19.880
And the property of
v being included in x

00:40:19.880 --> 00:40:24.660
is that all of its
non-neighbors appear after v.

00:40:24.660 --> 00:40:31.350
So the probability that v,
little v, is in the set x

00:40:31.350 --> 00:40:37.740
is equal to the
probability that v appears

00:40:37.740 --> 00:40:42.210
before all its non-neighbors.

00:40:52.300 --> 00:40:55.720
All v and its non-neighbors,
they're sorted uniformly.

00:40:55.720 --> 00:41:04.300
So the probability that this
occurs is exactly 1 over 1

00:41:04.300 --> 00:41:06.190
plus the number
of non-neighbors,

00:41:06.190 --> 00:41:08.320
which is n minus the degree of.

00:41:26.340 --> 00:41:28.980
Well, we know that
this graph G has

