no cliques of size r plus 1.

00:41:31.950 --> 00:41:40.720
So if we consider the expected
number of the size of x,

00:41:40.720 --> 00:41:43.600
on one hand, it is at most r.

00:41:43.600 --> 00:41:48.610
Because G K sub r plus 1-free.

00:41:48.610 --> 00:41:52.810
On the other hand, by
linearity of expectations,

00:41:52.810 --> 00:41:55.330
each vertex is included
with some probability.

00:41:55.330 --> 00:41:58.340
So the size of x in
expectation is just

00:41:58.340 --> 00:42:05.650
a sum of all of these individual
inclusion probabilities, which

00:42:05.650 --> 00:42:18.480
individually we've
